<Author>barbaraIreland
<Content>ann ireland 15th. june 2008 just returned from four day trip to Berlin. This hotel was ideal, really close to u bahn and handy for buses too., They offer the best breakfast you could imagine all sorts of cereals, juices ,and such a choice of fresh fruits also bacon sausage scrambled egg and too !. Sets you up for the day. The rooms are spotlessly clean and of ample size, as are the en suites. The front rooms face onto the busy road and can be noisy during the night .(there are only a few of these) insist on a room towards the back and it will be very peaceful all night.. The staff are helpful in finding some restaurants down nearby streets that you would really miss without help. A bonus is that down most of the side streets about 3/4 kilometre you will arrive at the riverside, which is a lovely walk. I felt it was a quiet safe area even in the evenings and you can actually walk t o the Brandenberg Gate from the Hotel. 
