<Author>PamjoHertfordshire
<Content>A gem of a hotel We were a group of 5 couples aged 58+ and chose the Hotel Tiergarten for its character, price and location. It is situated only 2 stops on the U-bahn from the Zoo station with the TXL airport bus stop a short walk away). Our flight landed at 10.05 a.m. Berlin time and we were in our hotel by 11.00 a.m.! Our rooms overlooked the internal courtyard and were very peaceful. We stayed for 4 nights between 16th - 20th April. The owner was extremely helpful and very friendly, as were his staff. There was a great deal of choice for breakfast and the only thing that could have improved our stay was perhaps tea/coffee making facilities in the room although we did have a mini bar. My husband and I had a room on the 2nd floor with ensuite bathroom. It was spotlessly clean and we had a daily maid service. Other members of our group had rooms in different parts of the hotel but they were of the same opinion regarding the high standard. The hotel has a lift and so taking luggage to our rooms was not a problem. It also has a luggage room which meant we were able to leave our cases at the hotel on our last day, until our early evening flight. I would recommend this hotel to anyone looking for quality at a reasonable price. 
