<Author>machar
<Content>Great hotel I and 14 of my friends stayed here the weekend before Xmas 2005 (apologies for the late review!). I organised the accommodation through the Berlin tourist office and checked the reviews on here. All of my friends thought this was a great hotel so there another 14 people backing this review! The hotel was based just down from the underground and was easy to find once you knew what side of the road you were on! The welcome was really nice and they were ready for us all arriving at once. We got to pick our rooms from a list so certain smaller groups could be together. The rooms were a good size with a decent sized bathroom. We had a shower and the shower tray was rather deep so if you have short legs like me be careful! The rooms were warm and cosy as were the beds so no complaints there.The hotel was based beside some good resturants and the pub a couple of doors down on the corner became our local and our meeting point. The highlight of this hotel must be the breakfasts. The buffet was like nothing I had ever seen before. Acres of food, everything you could imagine - fruit, meat, cheese, sweets, bread, rolls, cornflakes, fish, fruit salads piled up on different levels. It looked like a church harvest display. If you stocked up at breakfast you didn't need to eat until the evening.The staff were really nice and coped admirably with so many of us bumbling about and asking questions all the time.I would recommend this hotel to anyone (except those looking for 4 star luxury) and I would definitely go back! 
