<Content>Not as wonderful as suggested I just returned from a July 2006 trip to Germany, Poland and London. I moved around a lot and stayed at a lot of hotels. The Hotel Tiergarten was my first stop. This is NOT as wonderful as other reviews state. Parking (I had a rental car) is nearly impossible. The tiny lobby has nothing (it DOES have internet access, though) to offer and the elevator is your usual tiny luggage elevator that takes you to a very ordinary room. Ours was on the streetside, so it was VERY noisy all night since the hotel is on a main drag. And we had to keep the windows open, of course, since there's no AC as far as I can tell at any hotel in Europe. WARNING: I almost killed myself stepping out of the tiny corner shower, which is mounted about a foot off the bath floor with a tiny step out. Miss it, slip and you'll be sprawled on the floor like me, wondering if your trip is ruined by a broken ankle. It wasn't, but it was scary. Breakfasts are decent, but not as good as other hotels on the trip. All in all, a very average hotel. 
