<Content>Excellent and charming small hotel I stayed at this small hotel with my partner and with several colleagues from different European countries with whom I needed to arrange a meeting one weekend in November. I can recommend this hotel very strongly to anyone who wants to stay in an atmospheric and charming small hotel with excellent service. The hotel building is converted from a set of nineteenth century apartments in a commercial and residential area of central Berlin - a very good place to experience the atmosphere of everyday Berlin, away from the tourists. It is not a highly luxurious hotel, but very carefully run and convenient, with attention to every detail. Breakfast is generous and excellent. We wanted to hold a small meeting at the hotel, and the manager and staff could not have been more helpful and obliging. While several other Berlin hotels I contacted wanted to charge us at high rates for just using a meeting routine for 6 people (we needed no other facilities), the Tiergarten staff were very happy to make their breakfast room available for our meeting for most of the day free of charge, and were very flexible about supplying us with coffee at minimal charge whenever we wanted it. The Tiergarten is now definitely my hotel of choice in Berlin! 
