<Author>Lynda
<Content>Excellent transport connections away from tourist bustle. Stayed here a week, accompanying school group but would recommend it highly for families and individuals too. Large triples and quads make ideal for families. My single was a fair size with excellent lighting (a reading lamp at last!) and new bathroom. Incredible breakfast buffet with widest choice I've ever seen in 3 (or 4)star hotel. Staff are pleasant and helpful,with tips on transport, sights (and info on emergency room at hospital!) S-Bahn station Bellevue was nearby (pleasant walk by river then over the bridge) and we used it more than U-Bahn Turmstrasse which is right by the hotel. With S-Bahn you get to see the city and we found Friedrchstrasse a much less confusing station to connect at than Zoo. Both these stations 2 stops away. Short journeys (up to 3 stops) cost less: Kurzstreckenkarte. If you're doing more travelling the day ticket at 5.60 is better value (Kids up to 14 pay less). Even better value for group, Kleingruppenkarte at 14 euros covers 5 people for a day. Reception sells tickets and has maps of U  S-Bahn network, which you'll find essential! 
